Version: 0.1.11
Date: 2026-04-12

Changes:
- Fixed a P0 shell-tool hang where tool calls could wait indefinitely on `close`
  when parent processes exited but background descendants kept stdio open.
- Updated process settlement strategy across runtime shell execution paths to
  settle on `exit` first, with `close` as fallback:
  - `src/tools/builtin/bash.ts`
  - `src/tools/builtin/process_common.ts`
  - `src/verification/runner.ts`
- Added regression tests for background-child stdio inheritance scenarios,
  ensuring tool calls and verification checks return promptly.

Related commits:
- fix(runtime): settle shell executions on process exit to avoid background stdio hangs
